  "detailed_description": "This video captures a prenatal chiropractic adjustment session for a 31-week pregnant woman. The core meaning is the comprehensive demonstration of various chiropractic techniques, including leg length checks, lower back drops on a specialized table designed for pregnancy, mid-back and upper back adjustments, hip adjustments (similar to the Webster technique for pelvic balance), and extremity adjustments for ankles, knees, wrists, and elbows. The chiropractor also utilizes an activator tool for gentle neck adjustments. The session aims to enhance the mother's comfort and well-being during pregnancy, contributing to a healthier environment for the baby and a smoother delivery.",
